"version": "1.0.2",
"title": "5395: lordship, human and divine",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5395: lordship, human and divine",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture recognises that human beings exercise authority in various capacities and ways. However, it insists that all human authority derives ultimately from God himself.</p>\n<h2>Human lordship within society</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:42\">LUK 12:42</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The lordship of masters over their servants</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps123:2\">PSA 123:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:25\">MAT 18:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:19\">MAT 25:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:36\">LUK 12:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:3\">LUK 16:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:5\">EPH 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:9\">EPH 6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:22\">COL 3:22</a></p>\n<h3>The lordship of owners over their possessions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:23\">JDG 19:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:9\">MRK 12:9</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:40\">MAT 21:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:15\">LUK 20:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:33\">LUK 19:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:1\">GAL 4:1</a></p>\n<h3>The use of Lord (NIV ``Sir'') as a title of respect</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:63\">MAT 27:63</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:8\">LUK 13:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:21\">JHN 12:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:15\">JHN 20:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:30\">ACT 16:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:6\">1PE 3:6</a></p>\n<h2>Human lordship within the church</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:42-Mark10:45\">MRK 10:42–10:45</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:25-Matt20:28\">MAT 20:25–20:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:25-Luke22:27\">LUK 22:25–22:27</a></p>\n<h3>Christian lordship as a pastoral responsibility</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2-1Pet5:3\">1PE 5:2–5:3</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The lordship of God</h2>\n<h3>``Lord'' as a title for God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:14-Exod3:15\">EXO 3:14–3:15</a></strong> <em>In the NIV, “Lord” indicates a person with authority (this can be used of God) and “LORD” indicates Yahweh, the special Israelite name for God, revealed here to Moses.</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:3\">EXO 6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:6\">EXO 6:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1-Isa6:5\">ISA 6:1–6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:5-Isa45:8\">ISA 45:5–45:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:18\">ISA 45:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:20\">HOS 2:20</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:32\">LUK 1:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:9\">LUK 2:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:15\">REV 11:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev16:7\">REV 16:7</a></p>\n<h3>God is Lord of heaven and earth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:5-Ps135:6\">PSA 135:5–135:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:25\">MAT 11:25</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:21\">LUK 10:21</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:2-Ps2:4\">PSA 2:2–2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps57:11\">PSA 57:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps97:9\">PSA 97:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:47\">DAN 2:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:24\">ACT 17:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:15\">1TI 6:15</a></p>\n<h2>The revelation of the lordship of God</h2>\n<h3>The word of the LORD is the authoritative revelation of God's lordship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:11\">EZK 3:11</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:25\">1PE 1:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:8\">ISA 40:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:2\">ISA 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:19\">ISA 45:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:2\">JER 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:9\">JER 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:3\">EZK 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek2:4\">EZK 2:4</a>ROM <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek12:19\">12:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:352\">DEU 32:352</a>CO <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:16-Deut6:18\">6:16–6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:12\">LEV 26:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:11\">ISA 52:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:34\">EZK 20:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:41\">EZK 20:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:14\">2SA 7:14</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:10\">JAS 5:10</a>ACT <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas8:25\">8:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:49\">ACT 13:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:36\">ACT 15:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:32\">ACT 16:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:10\">ACT 19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:20\">ACT 19:20</a></p>\n<h3>God's lordship will be revealed to all on the day of the LORD</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:11-Isa2:12\">ISA 2:11–2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:17\">ISA 2:17</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:14-Zeph1:18\">ZEP 1:14–1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:6\">ISA 13:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:9-Isa13:11\">ISA 13:9–13:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:1-Joel2:2\">JOL 2:1–2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:18-Amos5:20\">AMO 5:18–5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:5\">1CO 5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:2\">1TH 5:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:2\">2TH 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:101\">2PE 3:101</a>CO <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:8\">1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:14\">2CO 1:14</a></p>",
